h3. Summary
When using the [Korean Language Pack for JIRA Core 7.2.0|https://translations.atlassian.com/dashboard/download?lang=ko_KR#/JIRA%20Core/7.2.0], the components page on a project will display a blank screen if there is more than one issue per component.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Install the [Korean Language Pack for JIRA Core 7.2.0|https://translations.atlassian.com/dashboard/download?lang=ko_KR#/JIRA%20Core/7.2.0];
# Set the user language to korean;
# Create a component and add two (or more) issues to it;
# Access the *Components* page on the Project menu;

h3. Expected Results
All components are shown, indicating the number of issues per component;

h3. Actual Results
A blank screen is displayed as shown bellow:
 !Two issues on component.png|thumbnail! 

h3.Workaround
At this moment, changing the language pack is the only known workaround.

