h3. Problem Definition

Per documentation for [Creating issues and comments from email|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/creating-issues-and-comments-from-email-802592933.html], when the mail handler is configured to create new users from unrecognized email addresses, the new username is created as follows:

{quote}The username and email address of these newly created JIRA user accounts will be the email addresses specified in the From: fields of these received messages.{quote}

This can cause confusion when it is inconsistent whether a user was created via email and their username is their full Email, versus when a user was created via JIRA and their username does not necessarily have to be an email address.

h3. Suggested Solution

Allow for a configuration that determines whether the new username should have the domain stripped off ("@domain.com").
